problem_statement:
Unsupported page encoding when reading Parquet
Hi Team, We are unable to read some of the parquet files like aws2.parquet and complex.parquet from this repository

#### What happens?
When we trigger a select query such as select * from aws2.parquet limit 5, we are able to see **Unsupported page encoding when reading Parquet**

#### To Reproduce
1) Download the aws2.parquet file from https://github.com/duckdb/duckdb/blob/master/data/parquet-testing/aws2.parquet
2) Go to https://shell.duckdb.org/
3) Execute the **.files add** command to select the downloaded aws2.parquet file
4) Execute the **.files list** command to see the list of files uploaded (at present we only uploaded aws2.parquet)

This has been an issue for me as well. I checked the Parquet extension and the supported page encodings are limited. I worked around the problem by only using DuckDB supported encodings in my Parquet ETL process.

Per the latest Parquet extension source: https://github.com/duckdb/duckdb/blob/688abf6324397108fcc9e6f2dd388d04c0910586/extension/parquet/column_reader.cpp#L284

The only encodings currently supported are [Plain](https://github.com/apache/parquet-format/blob/master/Encodings.md#plain-plain--0), [Plain/RLE Dictionary](https://github.com/apache/parquet-format/blob/master/Encodings.md#dictionary-encoding-plain_dictionary--2-and-rle_dictionary--8), and [Delta](https://github.com/apache/parquet-format/blob/master/Encodings.md#delta-encoding-delta_binary_packed--5). Previously I was using a few others more appropriate for my data types and encountered the reported error. Note that DuckDB seems to read the metadata for columns with unsupported page encodings without issue.
